Myrmidon recieved Hydras' reply:
 
> Hydras laughted and said "It seems that Trelos is playing, let's help
> him  abit "and send an encoded message "can you send me the
> coordinates of the situation"

Bobbing his head once the eagle swooped once more around Atlantis and
then prepared to beam Hydras the co-ordinates when the chase took a
very different turn .... 

Myrmidon watches from above as:

> As the group reached the end of the street, it was obvious that they
> had reached a dead end.  Trelos sat on top of the railing facing the
> group.
> 
> The beast took a long look at the group, then turned around and
> jumped headfirst off the railing, down the 100 feet and into the 
> water.

Myrmidon transmitted the details to Hydras, "It would seem that this
Trelos is a more elusive prey then the Maximals had anticipated. Here
are the new co-ordinates." (sends co-ordinates of where Trelos impacted
the water) 

"By the way, is this Trelos ally or enemy?"

OOC: Note the Eagle has been swooping around Atlantis now almost in
search patturns, and behaving in a very odd almost uneagle like
fashion. 

Preston
(Myrmidon)
